<section>
<title>Summary</title>
<p>
The various equations introduced in this chapter are summarized as
in <xref ref="table_rel-defs">Table</xref>.
</p>
<table xml:id="table_rel-defs" >
<caption>Relativistic formulas for energy and momentum.</caption>
<tabular>
<row bottom="minor"><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell></row>
<row><cell><em>Definition of momentum:</em></cell><cell>
<me>
  \vec p =\frac{m\vec u}{\sqrt{1-u^2/c^2}}
</me>
</cell><cell><em>Definition of energy:</em></cell><cell>
<me>
  E =\frac{mc^2}{\sqrt{1-u^2/c^2}}
</me>
</cell></row>
<row><cell><em>Energy in terms of momentum and mass:</em></cell><cell>
<me>
  E^2 = p^2c^2 + m^2c^4
</me>
</cell><cell><em>Velocity in terms of energy and momentum:</em></cell></row>
<row><cell>(See Problem \arabic{chapter}. <xref ref="prob_rel-u-p-e"></xref>.)</cell><cell>
<me>
  \vec{u} = \frac{\vec{p}c^2}{E}
</me>
</cell></row>
<row><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell></row>
<row><cell><em>Definition of kinetic energy:</em></cell><cell>
<me>
  K = E - mc^2
</me>
</cell><cell><em>Energy in terms of momentum for 
zero-mass particle:</em></cell><cell>
<me>
  E = \left|\vec{p}\right|c
</me>
</cell></row>
<row><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell></row>
<row bottom="minor"><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell><cell></cell></row>
</tabular>
</table>
</section>
